                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Thu, 5 Nov 2015 14:51:05 +0000</created>
                <updated>Tue, 16 Apr 2019 09:30:51 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Fri, 6 Nov 2015 09:55:23 +0000</resolved>
                                        <fixVersion>3.0.0</fixVersion>
                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>3</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14991759" author="beobal" created="Thu, 5 Nov 2015 14:55:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/riptano/cassandra-dtest/pull/643&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;This pull request&lt;/a&gt; adds a dtest to expose this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14991769" author="slebresne" created="Thu, 5 Nov 2015 15:01:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s right, the value skipping doesn&apos;t play well with read repair. In fact, that&apos;s also a problem for the &quot;hoisting&quot; of rows we sometime do on the query-by-names path. We could fix both places to ignore those &quot;skipped values&quot;, which would be fine, but we want to release 3.0 and I want to 1) make sure there isn&apos;t some other places I&apos;ve missed and 2) take the time to figure the safest way to deal with this. So for now, I&apos;ve pushed a very trivial patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/pcmanus/cassandra/commits/10655&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; to just disable that value skipping. That&apos;s &quot;only&quot; an optimization after all, and we&apos;re not worth off than in any previous version without it, so it&apos;s totally acceptable for 3.0. I&apos;ll create a followup ticket to re-enable in a cleaner/non broken way.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14991776" author="beobal" created="Thu, 5 Nov 2015 15:06:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 new test passes with the patch applied.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14991790" author="slebresne" created="Thu, 5 Nov 2015 15:16:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For info, the followup is &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10657&quot; title=&quot;Re-enable/improve value skipping&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-10657&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-10657&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Otherwise, I&apos;ve started unit test on the patch and will wait on the result to commit. Probably won&apos;t wait on the dtests though since I don&apos;t think they are yet already migrated to the new python driver and honestly, the risk of breaking something with this patch is very very minimal.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14993448" author="slebresne" created="Fri, 6 Nov 2015 09:55:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Unit tests looked good so committed, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
